name: UnmodifiableListView
comment:
An unmodifiable collection/dart-core.List view of another List.

The source of the elements may be a collection/dart-core.List or any collection/dart-core.Iterable with efficient collection/dart-core.Iterable.length and collection/dart-core.Iterable.elementAt.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

[].comment: Returns the object at the given collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.[].index in the list or throws a dart-core.RangeError if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.[].index is out of bounds.

length=.name: length=
length=.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an Iterator that iterates over this Iterable object.

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

reversed.name: reversed
reversed.comment: Returns an dart-core.Iterable of the objects in this list in reverse order.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

[]=.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

add.name: add
add.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.any.test. Returns false otherwise.

asMap.name: asMap
asMap.comment:
Returns an unmodifiable dart-core.Map view of this.

The map uses the indices of this list as keys and the corresponding objects as values. The Map.keys dart-core.Iterable iterates the indices of this list in numerical order.

List<String> words = ['fee', 'fi', 'fo', 'fum'];
Map<int, String> map = words.asMap();
map[0] + map[1];   // 'feefi';
map.keys.toList(); // [0, 1, 2, 3]

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if the collection contains an element equal to collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.contains.element.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.elementAt.indexth element.

The collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than collection/dart-core.Iterable.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.elementAt.index elements in this.

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.every.test. Returns false otherwise.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

fillRange.name: fillRange
fillRange.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

getRange.name: getRange
getRange.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable that iterates over the objects in the range collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.start inclusive to collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.end exclusive.

An error occurs if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.end is before collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.start.

An error occurs if the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.start and collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.getRange.end are not valid ranges at the time of the call to this method. The returned dart-core.Iterable behaves like skip(start).take(end - start). That is, it does not throw exceptions if this changes size.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
Iterable<String> range = colors.getRange(1, 4);
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue, orange'
colors.length = 3;
range.join(', ');  // 'green, blue'

indexOf.name: indexOf
indexOf.comment:
Returns the first index of collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.indexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list from index collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.indexOf.start to the end of the list. The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.indexOf('re');    // 1
notes.indexOf('re', 2); // 3

Returns -1 if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.indexOf.element is not found.

notes.indexOf('fa');    // -1

insert.name: insert
insert.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

insertAll.name: insertAll
insertAll.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.join.separator string.

lastIndexOf.name: lastIndexOf
lastIndexOf.comment:
Returns the last index of collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.element in this list.

Searches the list backwards from index collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.start to 0.

The first time an object o is encountered so that o == element, the index of o is returned.

List<String> notes = ['do', 're', 'mi', 're'];
notes.lastIndexOf('re', 2); // 1

If collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.start is not provided, this method searches from the end of the list./Returns

notes.lastIndexOf('re');  // 3

Returns -1 if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastIndexOf.element is not found.

notes.lastIndexOf('fa');  // -1

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.map.f multiple times on the same element.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

remove.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

removeAt.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

shuffle.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.skipWhile.test.

sort.name: sort
sort.comment: This operation is not supported by an unmodifiable list.

sublist.name: sublist
sublist.comment:
Returns a new list containing the objects from collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.start inclusive to collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.end exclusive.

List<String> colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink'];
colors.sublist(1, 3); // ['green', 'blue']

If collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.end is omitted, the collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.length of this is used.

colors.sublist(1);  // ['green', 'blue', 'orange', 'pink']

An error occurs if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.start is outside the range 0 .. length or if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.sublist.end is outside the range start .. length.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.take.n elements.

It is an error if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.where.test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.where.test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function collection/dart-pkg-collection-wrappers.UnmodifiableListView.where.test multiple times on the same element.
